              <additions>
                <p/>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="p2addition1">
                    <locus from="5a"/>
                    <p>On fol. 5a there is a note, stating that the priest <persName ref="">John</persName>, the son of <persName ref="">Macarius</persName>, abbat of the Syrians in the desert of <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/289">Scete</placeName>, helped to bind this book, <date when-custom="1205" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 1205</date>, <date when="0894" calendar="Gregorian">A.D. 894</date>.</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܐܫܬܘܬܦ ܒܕܘܒܩܐ ܗܢܐ ܝܘܚܢܢ ܚܛܝܐ ܘܒܨܝܪܐ ܩܫܝܫܐ ܒܪ ܡܩܪܝ ܪܝܫ ܕܝܪܐ ܕܣܘܪ̈ܝܝܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܣܩܝܛܝܣ. ܟܠ ܕܩ̇ܪܐ ܒܗ̣ ܢܨܠܐ ܥܠܘܗܝ ܏ܘܫ. ܟܬܒܬܝ ܗܠܝܢ ܒܫܢܬ ܐܠܦ ܘܡܬܝܢ ܏ܘܗ ♰ </quote></p></item><!-- A special shape of cross needs to replace the one which ends this quote. -->
                  <item n="2" xml:id="p2addition2">
                    <locus from="5a"/>
                    <p>Underneath this, the same <persName ref="">John</persName> has written in Coptic:</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="cop"><!-- Insert Coptic here --></quote></p>
                    <p><quote>I pray the God of my fathers, remember my littleness, I <persName ref="">John</persName> the little, priest, son of….<persName ref="">Macarius</persName>…..(?). May Christ Jesus our Lord forgive me all my sins, because I have laboured at this holy book of Abba <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/483">Evagrius</persName>.</quote></p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions>
